{"questionId":"17450","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A body moves in a straight line such that its velocity,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"v\\,{\\text{m}}{{\\text{s}}^{ - 1}}\">\n  <mi>v</mi>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>m</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>s</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, after <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;seconds is given by <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"v = 2\\,{\\text{sin}}\\left( {\\frac{t}{{10}} + \\frac{\\pi }{5}} \\right)\\csc \\left( {\\frac{t}{{30}} + \\frac{\\pi }{4}} \\right)\">\n  <mi>v</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>10</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mi>π</mi>\n        <mn>5</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>csc</mi>\n  <mo>⁡</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>30</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mi>π</mi>\n        <mn>4</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0 \\leqslant t \\leqslant 60\">\n  <mn>0</mn>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mn>60</mn>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p>The following diagram shows the graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"v\">\n  <mi>v</mi>\n</math></span> against <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span>. Point <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{A}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>A</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> is a local maximum and point <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{B}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>B</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> is a local minimum.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/cde4e8351e2c1ba62fcc7f486e0a781800e178a7.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Determine the coordinates of point <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{A}}\"> <mrow> <mtext>A</mtext> </mrow> </math></span> and the coordinates of point <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{B}}\"> <mrow> <mtext>B</mtext> </mrow> </math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{A}}\\left( {7.47{\\text{, }}2.28} \\right)\"> <mrow> <mtext>A</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mn>7.47</mn> <mrow> <mtext>,&nbsp;</mtext> </mrow> <mn>2.28</mn> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>&nbsp; and&nbsp; <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{B}}\\left( {43.4{\\text{,}} - 2.45} \\right)\"> <mrow> <mtext>B</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mn>43.4</mn> <mrow> <mtext>,</mtext> </mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mn>2.45</mn> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17450","referenceCode":"19N.2.AHL.TZ0.H_9a.i","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Determine the coordinates of point A and the coordinates of point B .","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.9—Kinematics problems"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}